    2037/ EA56:
    2038/ EA56:
    2039/ EA56:                ;****************
    2040/ EA56:                ;*  assem(addr) -68HC11 line assembler/disassembler.
    2041/ EA56:                ;*       This routine will disassemble the opcode at
    2042/ EA56:                ;*<addr> and then allow the user to enter a line for
    2043/ EA56:                ;*assembly. Rules for assembly are as follows:
    2044/ EA56:                ;* -A '#' sign indicates immediate addressing.
    2045/ EA56:                ;* -A ',' (comma) indicates indexed addressing
    2046/ EA56:                ;*       and the next character must be X or Y.
    2047/ EA56:                ;* -All arguments are assumed to be hex and the
    2048/ EA56:                ;*       '$' sign shouldn't be used.
    2049/ EA56:                ;* -Arguments should be separated by 1 or more
    2050/ EA56:                ;*       spaces or tabs.
    2051/ EA56:                ;* -Any input after the required number of
    2052/ EA56:                ;*       arguments is ignored.
    2053/ EA56:                ;* -Upper or lower case makes no difference.
    2054/ EA56:                ;*
    2055/ EA56:                ;*       To signify end of input line, the following
    2056/ EA56:                ;*commands are available and have the indicated action:
    2057/ EA56:                ;*   <cr>      - Finds the next opcode for
    2058/ EA56:                ;*          assembly.  If there was no assembly input,
    2059/ EA56:                ;*          the next opcode disassembled is retrieved
    2060/ EA56:                ;*          from the disassembler.
    2061/ EA56:                ;*   <lf><+>   - Works the same as carriage return
    2062/ EA56:                ;*          except if there was no assembly input, the
    2063/ EA56:                ;*          <addr> is incremented and the next <addr> is
    2064/ EA56:                ;*          disassembled.
    2065/ EA56:                ;*    <^><->   - Decrements <addr> and the previous
    2066/ EA56:                ;*          address is then disassembled.
    2067/ EA56:                ;*    </><=>   - Redisassembles the current address.
    2068/ EA56:                ;*
    2069/ EA56:                ;*       To exit the assembler use CONTROL A or . (period).
    2070/ EA56:                ;*Of course control X and DEL will also allow you to abort.
    2071/ EA56:                ;*** Equates for assembler ***
    2072/ EA56: =$0            PAGE1           EQU   $00             ;values for page opcodes
    2073/ EA56: =$18           PAGE2           EQU   $18
    2074/ EA56: =$1A           PAGE3           EQU   $1A
    2075/ EA56: =$CD           PAGE4           EQU   $CD
    2076/ EA56: =$0            IMMED           EQU   $0              ;addressing modes
    2077/ EA56: =$1            INDX            EQU   $1
    2078/ EA56: =$2            INDY            EQU   $2
    2079/ EA56: =$3            LIMMED          EQU   $3              ;(long immediate)
    2080/ EA56: =$4            OTHER           EQU   $4
    2081/ EA56:
    2082/ EA56:                ;*** Rename variables for assem/disassem ***
    2083/ EA56: =$C1           AMODE           EQU   TMP2            ;addressing mode
    2084/ EA56: =$C2           YFLAG           EQU   TMP3
    2085/ EA56: =$C3           PNORM           EQU   TMP4            ;page for normal opcode
    2086/ EA56: =$BE           OLDPC           EQU   PTR8
    2087/ EA56: =$B0           PC              EQU   PTR1            ;program counter
    2088/ EA56: =$B2           PX              EQU   PTR2            ;page for x indexed
    2089/ EA56: =$B3           PY              EQU   PTR2+1          ;page for y indexed
    2090/ EA56: =$B4           BASEOP          EQU   PTR3            ;base opcode
    2091/ EA56: =$B5           CLASS           EQU   PTR3+1          ;class
    2092/ EA56: =$B6           DISPC           EQU   PTR4            ;pc for disassembler
    2093/ EA56: =$B8           BRADDR          EQU   PTR5            ;relative branch offset
    2094/ EA56: =$BA           MNEPTR          EQU   PTR6            ;pointer to table for dis
    2095/ EA56: =$BC           ASSCOMM         EQU   PTR7            ;subcommand for assembler
    2096/ EA56:
